<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width="95%"><TR><td bgcolor="#ffffff"><TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="100%"><TR bgcolor="#000080"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#ffffff" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#DEDFDF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Troy1x</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I am a Level 16 Mage on Luclin and I need some serious help!!!!! I Have a Friend who is A level 16 Necro, he is starting to piss me off because he is bragging that he will kick my ass in a duel. I want to show him up so can someone help me out. I need to know what pet I showed use and the tactics and precautions I show Take. I want to kick his ass yet I don't want to get my ass kicked so can some fellow mage help me out!!<P>-Septar Level 16 Mage, Luclin</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#F7F7F7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">h8necros</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">16 is a strong level for necros. They have 3 good dots they can stack on you.<P></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#DEDFDF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Stickup Yohands</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">heres the strategy i always use.<BR>1) start fight at the maximum casting distance from him.<BR>2)sick pet (earth pet) with dmg shield if possible<BR>3) run out of his casting range and continue running till your pet cleans his pets clock.<BR>4) your pet starts hitting him and you start throwing bolts at him (hopefully your pet roots him too)<P>this is the really important part, ALWAYS stay out of his casting range, if he gets a few spells on you your dead, keep cancel magic memmed just incase he gets engulfing darkness off.<BR>I beat a level 51 necro with splurt on lvl 49 without taking a single point of damage, if he cant cast on you he cant hurt you and your pet will kill his every time one on one.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#F7F7F7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Zebanar01</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Use your Bolt spells as they effectively have 1/3rd more range than other spell types. </FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#DEDFDF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Comacosi</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Bah, Use air pet!</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#F7F7F7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Mirtzam</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Yes one on one your pet will win....but if you are staying out of his casting range what keeps him from attackin your pet along with his pet? I think your best pet is to get up your resits, use cancel magic, have a pet heal memmed, make sure pet survives (make sure you survive as well). Necros are great soloers and duelers, there biggest weakness is they arn't really good in groups...</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#DEDFDF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Stickup Yohands</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">if you stay out of his casting range and throw bolts at him he is definately not gonna fight your pet while being killed by bolts, he'll start chasing you so you run until the pets are done if he fears your pet cancel magic him(with the free charge from your staff) if possible otherwise cast the spell.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#F7F7F7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">me</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">How can your pet kill a necro pet when its snared and feared?  Dueling a necro is risky business.  If snare, fear or root sticks you are toast.  Bond of death is unresistable and if they get it off you are toast  <IMG SRC="http://forums.castersrealm.com/eq/smile.gif">.  <P>Often the necro will cast harmshield and you won't know it.  3 bubs of mana later, you will be in trouble  <IMG SRC="http://forums.castersrealm.com/eq/smile.gif">.<P>Also, if you die from a dot, and you will if they land any good ones, you lose exp.<P>Duel a melee class instead  <IMG SRC="http://forums.castersrealm.com/eq/smile.gif">.<P></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#DEDFDF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Dimuyen</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Also don't forget to use your phantom armor series.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#F7F7F7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Stickup Yohands</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">in this particular case hes fighting a lvl 16 necro i.e. no harmshield.  just make sure to dispel your pet the second you see it feared unless your confident enough you can finish him off with the next dd</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#DEDFDF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Midian</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">necros aren't so bad if you are ready for them.  remember that although he can beat your pet down, you can hide out from him while your pet fights his. (i like earth for this).  if you can sneak in for a pet heal now and then youll win.  if not, run off and summon a new pet.  itll take him a lot of mana to kill two pets, and his pet wont be able to hold out through two of yours.  once his pet is done, hes screwed.  oh yea, dam shield your pet too.  always run towards him while hes casting so the game calls his dotting kiting and reduces the damage for ya.  at that level, id buy a stein of moggok and then nothing he does to you is scary, youll have a ton of disease resistance.  necros aren't the invincables in duels they think they are, and once youve convinced yourself of that your all set up to win.  use invis to your advantage while his pet is tied up, get behind him and behind a couple of trees, you can nuke him up a bit and then run oot of range for a while.  hell probalby beat you the first time you duel, but by the second you will know all his tricks.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#F7F7F7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Segal</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">A good help, when asking PvP questions, is to ask someone who actually PvP's.<P>First off, don't worry about Harmshield as "me" said, since it's a level 20 necro spell. <P>If you want to humiliate him, pull up an earth pet, give it damage shield and start the duel. Put your pet on his (it'll happen anyways) and start UNLOADING your level 8 Shock of Blades on him. This spell has a 2 second cast time, instant recast and most importantly INTERRUPTS casting. A necro that can't cast spells is a dead necro.  Be ready for him to kick off a shadowstep in desperation. If he does, and you get the "target out of range" message, fire off a bolt. If you get the "you don't see your target here" message, leave attack on and turn til you get the "out of range" message and fire bolts at him. Then try to cycle in SoB in case he tries to get back into range.<P>His pet will be dead pretty soon, and you'll be at an advantage. <P>For an insurance policy, buy some crystallized pumice from a vendor (vendors that sell potions etc sell pumice). It has charges of nullify magic which will strip off all magic based DoT's he casts on you (Heat Blood, Heart Flutter, Darkness). To start the fight, make sure your top "buff slot" is open by casting a DS on yourself, then buffing, and cancelling the DS. Pumice removes effects from the top down.<P>However, this isn't really necessary if you stick to SoB. Your friend will die with full mana.<P>Don't forget to screencap it, it's the "-" key on your keypad.<P>A properly played mage can gank a necro pretty easily in a duel, depending on levels.<P><BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#DEDFDF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Lunasicc</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">This last strategy is your best bet if  you ask me.<BR>It works for me, but I always wonder why they don't chain lifetap. <P>Is lifetap as fast?<P><BR>btw blade spells are a must for pvp, even the low level ones.<BR>(what can a caster do if they can't cast?<BR></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE></td></tr></table> 
</FONT>
